[[File:UMTRAP 45 075 (27467610576).jpg|thumb|right|240px|Removal of uranium contamination at an UMTRA Project site]] The '''Uranium Mill Tailings Remedial Action''' (UMTRA) Project was created by the [[United States Department of Energy]] (DOE) to monitor the cleanup of uranium mill tailings. In 1978 the [[US Congress]] passed the [[Uranium Mill Tailings Radiation Control Act]] (UMTRCA) which tasked the DOE with the responsibility of stabilizing, disposing, and controlling uranium mill tailings and other contaminated material at uranium mill processing spread across 10 states and at approximately 5,200 associated properties.<ref name="nrc">{{cite web |url = http://www.eia.doe.gov/cneaf/nuclear/page/umtra/title1sum.html |title = Fact Sheet on Uranium Mill Tailings |accessdate = 2011-01-26 |year = 2006 |work = [[US Nuclear Regulatory Commission]] Fact Sheets |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101216131009/http://www.eia.doe.gov/cneaf/nuclear/page/umtra/title1sum.html |archive-date = 2010-12-16 |dead-url = yes |df = }}</ref> Under UMTRCA, the DOE created UMTRA to decommission 24 uranium mills and dispose of their residual mill tailings.<ref name="rmoa">{{cite web | url = http://www.eia.gov/nuclear/umtra/ | title = Uranium Mill Sites Under the UMTRA Project | accessdate = 2016-05-23 | year = 1999 | work = [[Energy Information Administration]] Independent Statistics and Analysis}}</ref>
